# /etc/cron.d/catalyst — Oubliette release engineering automated build schedule
#
# INSTALLATION
#   cp /opt/gentoo/oubliette-releng/config/cron.d/oubliette-relen /etc/cron.d/oubliette-relen
#   chmod 644 /etc/cron.d/oubliette-relen
#
# OVERVIEW
#   Two jobs are scheduled:
#
#   1. PURGE (weekly, Sunday 01:00)
#      Removes old catalyst artifacts, keeping the 2 newest build sets and
#      3 newest portage snapshots.  Runs weekly regardless of whether the
#      build fired automatically or was triggered manually, so disk space is
#      reclaimed on a predictable schedule.
#
#   2. BUILD (quarterly, 1st of Jan/Apr/Jul/Oct at 02:00)
#      Fetches the latest Gentoo seed stage3, rebuilds all oubliette hardened
#      stages via catalyst, and re-indexes the binary package cache.
#      To switch to monthly builds, change "1 1,4,7,10" to "1 *" in the
#      build job line below.
#
#   The purge runs one hour before the build so disk space is freed before
#   a new build starts.  If you reschedule the build, keep the purge at
#   least one hour earlier.
#
# EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS
#   ADMIN_EMAIL below controls two independent notification channels:
#
#   a) Script-level email (--mailto flag):
#      - oubliette-build.sh sends a failure alert (with the last 100 lines
#        of the build log) if the build exits non-zero.
#      - oubliette-build.sh sends a success summary listing every new stage
#        tarball and ISO produced by the run.
#      - purge-previous-catalyst sends a short failure alert if it exits
#        non-zero.
#      Set ADMIN_EMAIL to an address to enable these.  Leave it empty to
#      silence script-level email entirely.
#
#   b) Cron-level email (MAILTO):
#      Any output that escapes the scripts' own log redirection (e.g. an
#      unexpected crash before --logfile takes effect) is emailed by cron
#      to MAILTO.  This is set to ADMIN_EMAIL below so both channels go to
#      the same address, but you can set them independently.
#
#   To disable all email: set both ADMIN_EMAIL and MAILTO to empty strings.
#
# LOGS
#   Build output is appended to /var/log/oubliette/build.log.
#   Purge output is appended to /var/log/oubliette/purge.log.
#   See config/logrotate.d/oubliette-relen for the companion logrotate rule.
#
# MANUAL TEST RUNS
#   Dry-run purge (shows what would be removed, no deletions):
#     /opt/gentoo/oubliette-releng/tools/purge-previous-catalyst --dry-run
#
#   Full build with email and logging (same flags as the cron job):
#     /opt/gentoo/oubliette-releng/tools/oubliette-build.sh \
#         --mailto you@example.com \
#         --logfile /var/log/oubliette/build.log

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin

# Recipient for failure alerts and build summaries.
# Set to an email address, "root", or leave empty to disable script email.
ADMIN_EMAIL=root

# Cron sends unexpected output (crashes before log redirect) here.
MAILTO=root

# ┌── minute (0-59)
# │  ┌── hour (0-23)
# │  │  ┌── day of month (1-31)
# │  │  │  ┌── month (1-12)
# │  │  │  │           ┌── day of week (0=Sun … 6=Sat)
# │  │  │  │           │  ┌── user
# │  │  │  │           │  │     ┌── command
# │  │  │  │           │  │     │

# Weekly: purge old catalyst artifacts every Sunday at 01:00.
# --tmp removes leftover build chroots; safe when catalyst is not running.
0 1 * * 0 root /opt/gentoo/oubliette-releng/tools/purge-previous-catalyst --tmp --mailto "${ADMIN_EMAIL}" >> /var/log/oubliette/purge.log 2>&1

# Quarterly: build stages on the 1st of Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct at 02:00.
# To switch to monthly builds, change "1 1,4,7,10" to "1 *".
0 2 1 1,4,7,10 * root /opt/gentoo/oubliette-releng/tools/oubliette-build.sh --mailto "${ADMIN_EMAIL}" --logfile /var/log/oubliette/build.log
